ln this synod ot 1295 occurs a remarkable appeal to English patriotism. The F rench King, who had already seized Gascony, was threatening dire things against this country: Edward l says, “linguam Anglicanam, si conceptae iniquitatis proposito detestabili potestas correspondeat, quod Deus avortat! omnino de terra delere proponit.'' How well had the sense ol national life thriven in this country, when King Edward appeals so ! It is another evidence ol his wise sagacity; he accepted the victory oi the English language over the Norman F rench.
